headline: Tech Investors Turn on Zillow. Why Wall Street Still Likes the Stock.
summary: Zillow Group  is on the verge of reporting its first GAAP profitable year in over a decade.  Zillow’s  Class C shares on Monday closed at $54.28, slightly higher than the new 52-week closing low they set last week, according to FactSet data.  Analysts expect that the company will report GAAP earnings of seven cents on $2.58 billion in revenue for the full year in 2025, according to FactSet.
